-- Josef Ackermann Joins El-Erian on Kuwait’s NBK Advisory Board
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2012-07-16T11:52:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/josef-ackermann-joins-el-erian-on-kuwait-s-nbk-advisory-board.html
Josef Ackermann , the former chief
executive officer of  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) , has joined the  National
Bank of Kuwait  SAK’s International Advisory Board, the Gulf
state’s biggest lender said today in an e-mailed statement.  The 21-member International Advisory Board, which meets
annually, also includes Mohamed El-Erian, chief executive
officer of Pacific Investment Management Co., and former
Citigroup Inc. Senior Vice Chairman William Rhodes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
 fmacdonald4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
